# Code Quality — Self-Review Discipline

Self-review ALL code before marking a task done.

- Check for: edge cases, null safety, error handling, security
- No commented-out code, stubs, TODOs, FIXMEs in final output
- Stay within the task scope — do NOT refactor unrelated code
- Do NOT add features not explicitly requested
- Verify: does the code compile? Do existing tests still pass?
- Remove debug logging before finishing
